The paper deals with clustering of data points in metric space, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and has applications in data mining, information retrieval, and machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on the problem of balanced clustering (or capacitated clustering) in the streaming setting, which is a subfield of data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.AL). The paper also uses techniques from machine learning (cs.LG), data mining (cs.DM), information theory (cs.IT), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) to develop a single pass streaming algorithm for capacitated k-median and k-means problems in Euclidean space.
